### What problem does this feature solve?
Message components always show an icon, based on the type of message.  Unfortunately the icons do not mesh well with my apps existing design.  I would like to 'silence' the icon, or even better yet, provide my own Icon but there is no supported way in rendering a Message with anything except one of a few predefined icons. 

### What does the proposed API look like?
Two proposals: 

1. Allow overriding the default icons with a new `icons` config field.  undefined/null removes icon entirely.  See https://github.com/ant-design/ant-design/blob/master/components/message/index.tsx#L41 

    message.config({
      icons: {
        info: undefined,
        success: 'another icon',
      }
    });

2. a separate Message type: 

    message.custom(content, [duration], *icon*, onClose)

where `icon` is ReactNode.


